        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 25 at 5:16PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 516 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Dryden, or 8 miles southwest of Imlay City, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Almont, Lakeville, Attica, Imlay City, Leonard, Metamora, Dryden,
Oxford, and Thornville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
